      • updateAtomicallyClasspathFiles

        protected def updateAtomicallyClasspathFiles(classpathFiles : List<File>,
                                             duplicateAvoider : Set<String>,
                                             isMandatory : boolean,
                                             warnIfMissed : boolean,
                                             files : Iterable<String>) : void 
        Description copied from class: AbstractSarlBatchCompilerMojo
        Update the classpath file list by adding the given files and ensuring they exists when it is necessary.
        Parameters:
        classpathFiles - the list of classpath files to update.
        duplicateAvoider - the set of files that are already inside the classpath.
        isMandatory - indicates if the must be physically present on the disk. If true and the given file does not exist, it is created by using File.mkdirs().
        warnIfMissed - indicates if a warning must be generated if the files are missed from the disk.
        files - the list of files to add to the classpath.
        Since:
        0.12
